What I found that worked for me was to extend the **doFilter** method in the **MockFilterChain** class. Here&#39;s an example that will populate your response and **ContentCachingResponseWrapper**.
    
    private class FakeContentFilterChain extends MockFilterChain {

     private byte[] responseContent;

     FakeContentFilterChain(byte[] fakeContentToInject) {
      this.responseContent = fakeContentToInject;
     }

     // Need to short-circuit the filter call chain to fake populate the response
     @Override
     public void doFilter(ServletRequest arg0, ServletResponse arg1)
        throws IOException, ServletException {
      if (arg1 instanceof HttpServletResponse) {
        final HttpServletResponse httpServletResponse = (HttpServletResponse) arg1;
        httpServletResponse.setStatus(HttpStatus.OK.value());
        httpServletResponse.getOutputStream().write(responseContent);
      }
     }
    }


Then you can use it in your code as:

    FilterChain filterChain = new FakeContentFilterChain(&quot;test-body&quot;.getBytes());
    filter.doFilter(req, res, filterChain);

I used the similar approach to pre-write both request and response bodies for ContentCachingRequestWrapper and ContentCachingResponseWrapper respectively. It also allows to mock request, response and filter chain uniformly:

    import static org.mockito.Mockito.*;

    HttpServletRequest request = mock(HttpServletRequest.class);
    HttpServletResponse request = mock(HttpServletResponse.class);
    FilterChain filterChain = mock(FilterChain.class);

    doAnswer(invocation -&gt; {
            ContentCachingRequestWrapper requestWrapper = invocation.getArgument(0);
            ContentCachingResponseWrapper responseWrapper = invocation.getArgument(1);

            ByteArrayOutputStream requestContent = (ByteArrayOutputStream) ReflectionTestUtils.getField(requestWrapper, &quot;cachedContent&quot;);
            if (requestContent != null) {
                requestContent.write(&quot;{&#39;request-key&#39;: &#39;request-value&#39;}&quot;.getBytes());
            }
            FastByteArrayOutputStream responseContent = (FastByteArrayOutputStream) ReflectionTestUtils.getField(responseWrapper, &quot;content&quot;);
            if (responseContent != null) {
                responseContent.write(&quot;{&#39;response-key&#39;: &#39;response-value&#39;}&quot;.getBytes());
            }
            return null;
        }).when(filterChain).doFilter(any(ServletRequest.class), any(ServletResponse.class));

